org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust

Class Result<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorge_rico_vivas.rust.Result<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of contained value, if this value is set, then error must be null.
    E - Type of contained error, if this value is set, then value must be null.

    public class Result<T,E>
extends java.lang.Object
    A type used for returning and propagating errors. It represents two possible states:
    - Ok(T), representing success and containing a value.
    - Err(E), representing error and containing an error value.

    This is a port and Java adaptation of the Rust's Rust's Result Type.

      • from

        public static <T> Result<T,java.lang.Exception> from(java.util.concurrent.Callable<T> valueGetter)
        Generates a Result<T,Exception> which will be Ok(Value) if valueGetter gives a value, or Err(Exception) if an exception is thrown while trying to get said value.

        Example: 
        
 public class Main {
     public static void main(String[] args) {
         // Tries to read from a file that doesn't exist
         Result<List<String>, Exception> result = Result.from(
             () -> Files.readAllLines(new File("NonExistentFile").toPath())
         );
         Result<String, Exception> asString = result.map(Object::toString);
         String text = asString.unwrapOr("Path was wrong, please, contact the development team");
         System.out.println(text);
     }
 }
        Type Parameters:
        T - Value type.
        Parameters:
        valueGetter - Supplier giving the value.
        Returns:
        Result<T, Exception>.

      • mapOr

        public <U> U mapOr(U defaultValue,
                   java.util.function.Function<T,U> mapper)
        Returns the provided default (if Err), or applies a function to the contained value (if Ok).

        Arguments passed to map_or are eagerly evaluated; if you are passing the result of a function call, it is recommended to use map_or_else, which is lazily evaluated.

        Type Parameters:
        U - Type T transforms to as a return result.
        Parameters:
        defaultValue - a provided default which will be returned if this Result is Err(error).
        mapper - Maps the original value to another value as a return result.
        Returns:
        Value of the transformation from T to U if Result is Ok(value), otherwise, it returns the default value.

      • mapOrElse

        public <U> U mapOrElse(java.util.function.Supplier<U> defaultValue,
                       java.util.function.Function<T,U> mapper)
        Maps a Result<T, E> to U by applying fallback function default to a contained Err value, or function defaultValueGetter to a contained Ok value.

        This function can be used to unpack a successful result while handling an error.

        Type Parameters:
        U - Type T transforms to as a return result.
        Parameters:
        defaultValue - a provided supplier which results in default value which will be calculated and returned if this Result is Err(error).
        mapper - Maps the original value to another value as a return result.
        Returns:
        Value of the transformation from T to U if Result is Ok(value), otherwise, it calculates and returns the default value from the supplier.

      • unwrap

        public T unwrap()
         throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Returns the contained Ok value.

        Because this function may throw a RuntimeException, its use is generally discouraged. Instead, prefer to use pattern matching and handle the Err case explicitly, or call either unwrap_or or unwrap_or_else.

        Returns:
        the contained Ok value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the value is an Err, with an error message provided by the Err’s value.
